name: Jrmungandr
infoDetail:
[Traits]
[Jrmungandr] Uses a variety of abilities depending on its mode.

[Mode 1] It performs slow physical attacks that hit all targets at a low turn frequency.
[Mode 2] With a higher turn frequency, it begins to use a skill that increases its ATK. If the player's allies' abilities reach above a certain level, this same skill will reset their level.
[Mode 3] Both HP and ATK increase. If its HP falls below a certain threshold, it uses a skill that recovers HP as it attacks.

name: Ogre
infoDetail:
[Traits]
[Ogre] Grows very strong if 2 or more players' allies die, so come equipped with plenty of recovery skills to keep them alive.

Since it uses a skill that resets ability increases, you'll have better luck reducing the enemies' abilities than you will increasing your own.
It has an extremely high P.DEF and extremely low M.DEF, so you'll want to come equipped with as many polearm, projectile, and artifact weapons as possible.

name: Esse, the Investigator
infoDetail:
[Traits]

After changing modes, if any player ally's ability levels drop to -4 or lower, it can use a powerful skill.

[Strategy]

name: Kagami Mochi Ghost
infoDetail:
[Traits]
[Kagamimochi Ghost] Like ghost types, uses a lot of recovery skills. It will go for allies with the lowest DEF first.
If the number of nightmares dips too low, it releases its powerful "Happy New Year to You Too" attack. 

[Strategy]
Its M.DEF is very high, but its P.DEF is low.
Watch out when this enemy appears together with the New Year's Plant, since it can lower both your P.DEF and M.DEF.

[Strategy]
Its M.DEF is lower than it's P.DEF.
Watch out when this enemy appears together with the Kagami Mochi Ghost, since it likes to target weaker opponents.

infoDetail:

[Strategy]
Surtrs use powerful buffs, so have debuffs ready to counter. Gear with water affinity is recommended.

name: Ogre
infoDetail:
[Traits]
[Ogre] Grows very strong if 2 or more players' allies die, so come equipped with plenty of recovery skills to keep them alive.

Since it uses a skill that resets ability increases, you'll have better luck reducing the enemies' abilities than you will increasing your own.
It has an extremely high P.DEF and extremely low M.DEF, so you'll want to come equipped with as many polearm, projectile, and artifact weapons as possible.

name: Cake Spider
infoDetail:
[Traits]
At the start of the battle before it changes modes, it couples powerful attacks with skills that lower DEF. After that, it uses skills that increases its allies' M.ATK and DEF.
After changing modes, it couples powerful attacks with skills that lower DEF and follow that with a M.ATK that hits all targets.

[Strategy]
It's weak against magic attacks, so hit it with artifact, polearm, and projectile weapons.

name: Fafnir
infoDetail:
[Traits]
[Fafnir] Responds differently depending on its allies' ability levels.
In its third mode, it hits a single target with an extremely powerful P.ATK if any of its allies' ability levels drop to -4 or lower. Use skills that increase ability to keep their levels above this threshold.

Beware of this Nightmare's tendency to target the player with the lowest P.DEF.

name: Esse, the Investigator
infoDetail:
[Traits]
[Esse, the Investigator] Uses ranged magic attacks.
After changing modes, if any player ally's ability levels drop to -4 or lower, it can use a powerful skill.

[Strategy]
At the start of the wave, it uses a skill to reset all of your party members' ability increases. It won't use it again, however, so save them until after it performs that skill.

name: Jrmungandr
infoDetail:
[Traits]
[Jrmungandr] Uses a variety of abilities depending on its mode.

[Mode 1] It performs slow physical attacks that hit all targets at a low turn frequency.
[Mode 2] With a higher turn frequency, it begins to use a skill that increases its ATK. If the player's allies' abilities reach above a certain level, this same skill will reset their level.
[Mode 3] Both HP and ATK increase. If its HP falls below a certain threshold, it uses a skill that recovers HP as it attacks.

name: Fenrir
infoDetail:
[Traits]
[Mode 1] Its mode 1 attack is quick, but limited to just one target.
[Mode 2] It'll target the whole party, just once, and further speed up its movements.
[Mode 3] Its mode 3 attack is slow, but likely to hit two party members at once.
It has an extremely high P.DEF, to the point physical skills will only do 1 damage. 
[Strategy]
You'll want to use polearm, projectile and artifact weapons to have a better chance at winning.

[Strategy]

name: Cerberus
infoDetail:
[Traits]
Cerberus has an extremely high attack rate and can hit 3 targets at once. It can cancel any debuffs only once in each mode, and in Mode 2 it'll cancel one buff when its HP gets too low. In Mode 3, when his HP gets low he will deal a powerful attack on your entire party.

[Strategy] 
Its P.DEF will increase each time it changes modes, so magic attacks will be most effective. Also, because the number of targets Cerberus can hit decreases as its debuff levels increase, debuffing it with tomes works well.

and only deals physical attacks.
They mostly focus their aim on clerics.
 When a seere's HP drops below 10%, it will lash out with strong physical attacks.

name: Bael
infoDetail:
[Traits]
Bael's attacks have a wide aoe, and he specializes in debuffs. During modes 1-2, he'll use a lot of ranged attacks that cause debuffs, trying to decrease your skills. The lower his HP gets, the wider his range, so be careful. During mode 3, he'll buff himself before attacking your whole party repeatedly. He'll be open while he prepares to buff.

[Strategy]
The higher your characters' debuff level is, the less time you have until mode 3, so try to fight back with your own buffs.

At the start of the battle and after mode change, Prometheus will cut almost all of your HP in one shot and follow up by targeting the party with the powerful skill, "Endure it, if you can."

After the first fixed percentage damage attack, Prometheus won't attack for a while so heal as quickly as you can. After mode change, its M.DEF will rise so physical attacks will work best.

name: Jrmungandr
infoDetail:
[Traits]
[Jrmungandr] Uses a variety of abilities depending on its mode.

[Mode 1] It performs slow physical attacks that hit all targets at a low turn frequency.
[Mode 2] With a higher turn frequency, it begins to use a skill that increases its ATK. If the player's allies' abilities reach above a certain level, this same skill will reset their level.
[Mode 3] Both HP and ATK increase. If its HP falls below a certain threshold, it uses a skill that recovers HP as it attacks.

name: Ziz
infoDetail:
[Traits]
Ziz always brings its friends.
Ziz can't be defeated while its friends are present.
Greater Hound friends are quick to attack.
Greater Orc friends have high P.ATK.
Greater Golem friends have high ATK and DEF.
Dragon friends have high M.ATK.
In the final wave, when Ziz's buffs max out... You don't even wanna know.
[Strategy]
Counter Ziz with tome debuffs.

name: Ogre
infoDetail:
[Traits]
[Ogre] Grows very strong if 2 or more players' allies die, so come equipped with plenty of recovery skills to keep them alive.

Since it uses a skill that resets ability increases, you'll have better luck reducing the enemies' abilities than you will increasing your own.
It has an extremely high P.DEF and extremely low M.DEF, so you'll want to come equipped with as many polearm, projectile, and artifact weapons as possible.

name: Salesman (Wind)
infoDetail:
[Traits]
High HP and low DEF.
Besides physical attacks, it uses powerful debuffs on player's allies and buffs on itself.

[Strategy]
Its high HP and many buffs mean that it gets extremely strong if the battle drags on.
Its DEF is low, however, so target its weak spot to kill it quickly.
